title: Namibia elects its first female president in disputed elections
description: Vice-president Netumbo Nandi-Ndaitwah avoids runoff vote, as win extends Swapo party’s 34-year hold on powerNamibia has elected its first female leader, with Netumbo Nandi-Ndaitwah declared the winner of last week’s presidential election in a result that will extend the ruling Swapo party’s 34-year hold on power.Nandi-Ndaitwah, the current vice-president, won with 57% of the vote, according to official results, defying predictions that she might be forced into a runoff. Swapo has ruled the country since its independence from apartheid South Africa in 1990. Continue reading...
author: Rachel Savage and agencies in Windhoek

title: Joe Biden addresses America’s ‘original sin’ of slavery on Angola visit
description: US president remembers ‘stolen men and women and children brought to our shores’ and lauds American investment in countryJoe Biden addressed America’s history of enslavement in a speech on Tuesday at Angola’s National Museum of Slavery, calling it “our nation’s original sin” during a trip in which he also lauded recent US investment in the region.“We remember the stolen men and women and children who were brought to our shores in chains, subjected to unimaginable cruelty,” Biden said, as the sun set over the water behind him. Continue reading...
author: Rachel Savage Southern Africa correspondent and agencies

title: California school shooting: Two children hospitalised, suspected gunman dead
description: Two children were shot at Feather River School of Seventh-Day Adventists in Oroville, California, after a gunman opened fire on Wednesday. The shooter later died by suicide. The injured students were transported to hospitals, and their conditions remain unknown. Authorities believe the shooter had no connection to the school. Students were reunited with their families at a nearby church.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Hamas threatens to 'neutralise' hostages if Israel launches rescue op
description: Hamas warned it would "neutralize" hostages if Israel attempts another rescue operation like the one in June at Gaza's Nuseirat camp. An internal Hamas statement revealed the group instructed operatives to enforce stricter conditions for captives and prepare for immediate action if Israel intervenes.

title: Amnesty says Israel committing acts of genocide in Gaza. Here’s what to know.

title: A surprising turn in Syria's civil war
description: In the past week, the civil war in Syria reignited. Islamist rebels seized control of Aleppo, triggering a new phase in a years-long civil war. The Post’s Middle East bureau chief, Kareem Fahim, talks with host Elahe Izadi about why this moment matters.
author: Peter Bresnan, Savannah Robinson, Ariel Plotnick, Rennie Svirnovskiy, Monica Campbell, Reena Flores, Lucy Perkins
